\begin{align} a^2 - b^2 = 3\\ a \cdot b = 2 \end{align}
a = 2, b = 1
a^2=b^2+3
a^2 \cdot b^2 = 2^2
 (b^2 + 3) \cdot b^2 = 4\\ \rightarrow b^4 + 3b^2 = 4\\ \rightarrow b^2(b^2 + 3) = 4\\ 
\implies b^4+3b^2-4=0\iff (b^2+4)(b^2-1)=0
